----------------------
Linux notes
----------------------

See below for specific instructions for ubuntu and debian.  To make a
distribution tar file from the source code svn 1.1 branch, here is one way:

      svn checkout svn://macaulay2.math.uiuc.edu/Macaulay2/release-branches/1.1 M2-1.1
      cd M2-1.1
      make
      mkdir BUILD/opt
      cd BUILD/opt
      ../../configure --prefix=$PWD/installed \
          --enable-tarfile \
	  --enable-rpm \
          --enable-build-libraries="gc gdbm gmp mpfr readline ntl factory libfac lapack"

      svn co svn://Macaulay2.math.uiuc.edu/Macaulay2/trunk/M2 M2
      cd M2
      make
      mkdir BUILD/opt
      cd BUILD/opt
      ../../configure  --prefix=/home/mike/M2-builds/M2/BUILD/opt/installed' --enable-tarfile --enable-frobby


----------------------
MacOS X notes
----------------------
    The following are the steps we take to build a binary disk image for
    Macaulay2.  First, you must have installed the developer tools from apple:
    use either the packages that are on your system install DVD, or download
    from http://connect.apple.com.

    The script below downloads gc, gdbm, gmp, readline, ntl, factory and
    libfac, builds them, and then builds Macaulay2.  The libraries are
    statically linked in, to make installation simpler for most people.
    To make a 64 bit (intel) distribution disk image:

          svn checkout svn://macaulay2.math.uiuc.edu/Macaulay2/release-branches/1.1 M2-1.1
	  #  or for the main branch:
	  #svn co svn://Macaulay2.math.uiuc.edu/Macaulay2/trunk/M2 M2
	  cd M2-1.1
	  make
	  mkdir BUILD/opt64
	  cd BUILD/opt64
	  ../../configure --prefix=$PWD/installed \
                --enable-dmg \
                --enable-build-libraries="gc gdbm gmp mpfr readline ntl factory libfac" \
		--build=x86_64-apple-darwin \
		CC="gcc -m64" \
		CXX="g++ -m64"
          make
	  make install
	  # now there is a dmg file in BUILD/opt64
	  make check # optional, but recommended

   To make a 32 bit version (intel or ppc), use this instead:

	  svn co svn://Macaulay2.math.uiuc.edu/Macaulay2/trunk/M2 M2
	  cd M2
	  make
	  mkdir BUILD/opt32
	  cd BUILD/opt32
	  ../../configure --prefix=$PWD/installed \
                --enable-dmg \
                --enable-build-libraries="gc gdbm gmp mpfr readline ntl factory libfac"
          make
	  make install
	  # now there is a dmg file in BUILD/opt32
	  make check # optional, but recommended

    To make a 64 bit (intel) debug version:

	  svn co svn://Macaulay2.math.uiuc.edu/Macaulay2/trunk/M2 M2
	  cd M2
	  make
	  mkdir BUILD/debug64
	  cd BUILD/debug64
	  ../../configure --prefix=$PWD/installed \
	        --enable-debug --disable-optimize \
                --enable-build-libraries="gc gdbm gmp mpfr readline ntl factory libfac" \
		--build=x86_64-apple-darwin \
		CC="gcc -m64" \
		CXX="g++ -m64"
          make
	  make install
	  make check # optional, but recommended

    To make a 64 bit (intel) profile version (for use with gprof, and other tools):

	  svn co svn://Macaulay2.math.uiuc.edu/Macaulay2/trunk/M2 M2
	  cd M2
	  make
	  mkdir BUILD/profile64
	  cd BUILD/profile64
	  ../../configure --prefix=$PWD/installed \
	        --enable-profile \
                --enable-build-libraries="gc gdbm gmp mpfr readline ntl factory libfac" \
		--build=x86_64-apple-darwin \
		CC="gcc -m64" \
		CXX="g++ -m64"
          make
	  make install

