## cygwin notes #######################
#######################################
Installed cygwin from cygwin.org, by clicking on setup.exe
  Choosing the defaults for everything
  Choosing a mirror
  Installing all the default packages
Rerun setup.exe again from the web, although perhaps there is a way to do it locally)
  Installed (under editors): emacs, emacs-X11 (this gets an older version 21.1.2, but it seems fine)
Rerun setup.exe again from the web
  Added the URL:
    http://www.math.uiuc.edu/Macaulay2/Repositories/cygwin
  clicked on it
  chose (under Math), Macaulay2 (version 1.1-2)
  installed it
Back on windows XP desktop
Double-click on Cygwin icon -- should not need to do this!!
  M2
  setup() -- inside M2
  exit
At the prompt:
  startX
In the window that pops up:
  M2
Now f12 starts M2 fine.  The key f11 works as it should too.
Download firefox, make it the default browser

#######################################################
## Ubuntu source code install #########################
## These notes work the same for 32 or 64 bit Ubuntu ##
#######################################################
## Using the synaptic package manager, or
## apt-get install, get the following packages:
sudo apt-get install subversion
sudo apt-get install autoconf
sudo apt-get install libncurses5-dev
sudo apt-get install g++
sudo apt-get install g77
sudo apt-get install bison
sudo apt-get install flex

others to get:
sudo apt-get install emacs


